# Extra ignores for repomix on top of .gitignore.
#
# `.gitignore` excludes build artefacts but NOT the legalize-es submodule
# (it's a tracked path). Without these rules `repomix` would walk into
# `data/legalize-es/` and include ~1.7GB of Spanish law Markdown in the
# packed output — useless for code-focused LLM sessions and likely over
# any model's context window.

# Submodule: 1.7GB of legalize-es Markdown
data/legalize-es/

# Generated graph cache (regenerated locally, contains absolute paths)
.code-review-graph/

# Lockfiles — noisy and rarely useful in a code dump
package-lock.json
uv.lock
**/pnpm-lock.yaml
**/yarn.lock

# Build outputs that .gitignore catches but pin here for safety
frontend/dist/
landing/dist/
**/node_modules/

# Test snapshots / coverage
coverage/
.coverage
htmlcov/

